{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, in the future, we will investigate alternative prompting and personalization strategies (e.g., fine-tuning) for these smaller models.",
    "HallucinationsLLMs are subject to hallucinations, that is the generation of content that may be irrelevant, madeup, or inconsistent with the input data.",
    "In our use of LLMs, a hallucination may lead to a wrong prediction of the activity performed by the subject.",
    "It may also lead to an output that is not compliant with the instructions (e.g., predicting an activity not included in the given set or using a different format).",
    "The impact of the first is similar to the one due to miss-predictions obtained with classic data-driven models."
  ]
}